The travel video of Istanbul, Turkey

70
00:03:02,860 --> 00:03:03,860
was shot 80% handheld.

71
00:03:05,250 --> 00:03:06,250
For me, shooting handheld
is the quickest way

72
00:03:07,420 --> 00:03:08,420
to capture moments.

73
00:03:09,060 --> 00:03:10,060
To get the best handheld results,

74
00:03:11,040 --> 00:03:12,040
shooting in a high-frame rate,

75
00:03:12,570 --> 00:03:13,570
such as 60 frames-per-second,

76
00:03:14,840 --> 00:03:15,840
to then slow it down in post,

77
00:03:16,700 --> 00:03:17,700
which helps smoothen out the shots.

78
00:03:18,870 --> 00:03:19,870
Additionally, I like to add
image stabilization in post

79
00:03:21,720 --> 00:03:22,720
to get the best results possible.

80
00:03:23,810 --> 00:03:24,810
As you can see, you don't
necessarily need a gimbal

81
00:03:26,340 --> 00:03:27,340
to create dynamic looking shots.

82
00:03:28,160 --> 00:03:29,160
If you need to create static shots,

83
00:03:29,750 --> 00:03:30,750
such as a time-lapse,

84
